  m_Name: Napoleon_Wrasse
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::EndangeredFishDefinition
  fishName: Napoleon Wrasse
  scientificName: Cheilinus undulatus
  description: Also known as 'Mameng' in the Philippines. Large, colorful reef fish
    that can grow over 2 meters. Highly valued in live fish trade.
  status: 1
  iucnStatus: Endangered
  populationTrend: Decreasing
  habitat: Coral reefs in tropical waters, lagoons, and outer reef slopes
  distribution: Indo-Pacific region including Philippines, Indonesia, Malaysia, Australia,
    and Red Sea
  threats: Overfishing for live fish trade (especially to Hong Kong and China), habitat
    destruction, cyanide fishing, slow reproductive rate
  importance: Apex predator on coral reefs, maintains reef ecosystem balance, important
    for reef health and biodiversity
  conservationEfforts: Marine protected areas, fishing bans in some areas, CITES
    listing, size and catch limits, reef conservation programs
